<tt>Sat Jul 19 10:00:09 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
The Songs we sang and the love we left behind<br><br>
In early July 1967 1st platoon from India Company 3/7, 1st Marine division, was selected to make a re-supply  run to the Army's Special Forces Camp at Thuong Duc near the Laos/Cambodia border.  We had a running feud with them, actually it was more of a professional rivery. The old we're better then you are sort of thing guys do in war. <br><br>
On more then one occasion we responded to their need for help when they were getting overrun and in turn they, well they, ah, ah, well, they were there to keep us active in practicing our response time.<br><br>
Bro (Ronald Allan Moore) while we were there told us an old story that had been floating around. <br>
&quot;During the war for independence when it first started in Viet Nam, the ARVN's (Army of the Republic of South Vietnam) would run away from battle scenes, leaving their weapons behind. The Green Berets decided that they would train them to be better fighting men. Once they received military training from the Green Berets they would still run from a firefight, but now at least they took their weapons with them.&quot;  <br><br>
As we started to leave the Green Beret camp, Bro began to sing the Marine Corps version of the popular song called, &quot;The Ballad of the Green Berets.&quot; Many other Marines joined in singing and soon the song was loud enough for the Green Berets to hear. It was sung to the same tune and was a Marine response to their popular song.<br><br>
BALLAD OF THE U.S. MARINES<br><br>
We're the men, U. S. Marines <br>
Dirty, rough and fighting mean.<br>
From the States, we came this way<br>
Couldn't care less about the Green Beret.<br><br>
We stalk in paddies both night and day<br>
Don't need chutes or a green Beret.<br>
Have no wings upon our chests<br>
Fighting Marines, our country's best.<br><br>
With steel pots upon our heads<br>
We fight like mad and eat hot lead.<br>
Keep your cap and silver wings<br>
Take them home with all your things.<br><br>
We patrol and kill V.C.<br>
Fighting Cong to make men free,<br>
One hundred men, overrun today<br>
We saved them all, the Green Beret.<br><br>
I saw Marines who gave their lives<br>
So a Green Beret could live their life<br>
If I die in this far off land<br>
I hope to God, it's for a better man.<br><br>
While they jump and sing their songs<br>
We search the fields and kill the Cong.<br>
We're the men who fight each day<br>
Since &quot;75&quot; its been that way.<br><br>
(SOFTLY)<br>
Back at home, a young wife waits,<br>
Her Marine  has met his fate,<br>
He has died so others could live, <br>
For his land that's what he'll give.<br><br>
(LOUD)<br>
I know this song, won't be a hit<br>
But a good Marine don't give a SHIT!<br>
And when it comes to glory and fame<br>
We'll kick your ASS and take your NAME!<br><br>
Respectfully submitted <br><br>

